<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870402-0171 </DOCNO><HL> Cyprus Receives Coal JobFrom Niagara Mohawk</HL><DD> 04/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CYPM NMK </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Cyprus Minerals Co. said it was awarded a contract to provide 360,000 tons of coal a year for five years to Niagara Mohawk Power Corp., Syracuse, N.Y.    Terms weren't disclosed. Cyprus said it expects to sign the contract within 30 days and begin shipments to the utility this month.    Cyprus, a coal and minerals concern, already is shipping 240,000 tons of coal a year to Niagara Mohawk from its Emerald mine in southwestern Pennsylvania under a 1985 contract. </TEXT></DOC>